CTM 2.0 ADAUSD 8h Parameter Search

Created on: 13 August 2022, Last updated on: 13 August 2022
Home
  • Designed for desktop by Roman.
  • This document attempts to perform 2 parameters optimization on 8h ADAUSD using 'Cardano / US Dollar (calculated by TradingView) - 8h - BINANCE' chart data. These are 'Fast' and 'Slow' moving averages.
  • It uses Andrew's Python Backtester Example (version from 1-Aug-2022). Thank you, Andrew, for great contribution :-)
  • Such optimisation is CPU and RAM intense process. Therefore, it has been decided to perform larger parameter value steps (e.g. 6). You can explore in further detail in regions with dense values using TradingView Backtester (e.g. 35 66 which is missing from the charts below due to step=6 etc.)
  • CAUSION: Please take these results with a pinch of salt, Backtester script is still in the Beta version and potential bugs are still expected. This is for demonstration purposes.
